OL,3,CD-Day anniversary: Commemoration
OL,4,Cevents begin in Normandy
OL,6,FCommemorations to mark the 82nd
OL,7,Fanniversary of D-Day in Normandy have
OL,8,Fstarted, with French schoolchildren
OL,9,Fwalking across Juno Beach to mark H-
OL,10,FHour, the time at which British
OL,11,Fservicemen were deployed.
OL,13,FServing military personnel, the
OL,14,Fgrandson of British Commander Field
OL,15,FMarshal Montgomery and pipers from the
OL,16,FJedburgh Pipe Band marched with the
OL,17,Fschoolchildren on Saturday morning.
OL,19,FNearly 160,000 Allied troops landed on
OL,20,FJune 6 1944, to fight Nazi-occupied
OL,21,FFrance.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/5
