OL,3,CD-Day anniversary: Commemoration
OL,4,Cevents begin in Normandy
OL,6,FWhile the exact number of German
OL,7,Fcasualties is unknown, historians
OL,8,Festimate between 4,000 and 9,000 men
OL,9,Fwere killed, wounded or missing.
OL,11,FOn the Allied front, a total of 4,414
OL,12,Fdied.
OL,14,FThe Battle of Normandy, which followed
OL,15,Fthe landings, saw 73,000 Allied lives
OL,16,Flost with 153,000 men wounded.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/5
